## Delivery Guarantees

| Guarantee | What it means | Trade-off |
|---|---|---|
| **At-most-once** | Message delivered 0 or 1 times | May lose messages; fastest |
| **At-least-once** | Message delivered 1+ times | May duplicate; most common |
| **Exactly-once** | Message delivered exactly once | Hardest, slowest, most expensive |

### At-least-once + Idempotency = Effectively Exactly-Once

The practical approach: use at-least-once delivery and make your consumers **idempotent** — processing the same message twice has the same effect as processing it once.

```java
// Idempotent consumer pattern
@KafkaListener(topics = "orders")
public void processOrder(OrderEvent event) {
    // Check if already processed
    if (processedRepo.exists(event.getEventId())) {
        return; // already handled — skip
    }

    orderService.fulfill(event.getOrder());
    processedRepo.save(event.getEventId()); // mark as done
}
```
